"Written evidence from the British Association for Counselling and Psychotherapy (LTC 42)&#xa0;\nThe British Association for Counselling and Psychotherapy (BACP) would like to submit the following response to the Health Committee’s Inquiry into \nthe Management of \nL\nong-term \nC\nonditions\n (LTCs)\n.\n \nBACP’s response wi\nll\n focus on the interaction between mental health conditions and long-term physical health conditions and the use of psychological therapies\n to ameliorate the impact of psycho-bio-social problems\n.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nGeneral&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nChronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease &#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nDiabetes&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;As way of background, The British Association for Counselling and Psychotherapy (BACP) is the leading and largest professional body for counselling and psychotherapy in Europe, \nwith a membership of \nover 38\n,000 practitioners\n, \ndrawn from the various professional disciplines in the field of counselling and psychotherapy and based in a range of settings.\n \n&#xa0;\nAll BACP members are bound by the Ethical Framework for Good Practice for Counselling and Psychotherapy and within this, the Professional Conduct Procedure.\n&#xa0;\nShould the Committee be seeking further oral evidence, BACP would be delighted to provide additional information about \npsychological therapies long-term conditions.\n \n&#xa0;\nMay 2013\n Department of Health (2011) \nTalking Therapies: A four-year plan of action\n The Kings Fund (2012) \nLong-term conditions and mental health: The cost of co-\nmorbidities\n Office for National Statistics (2008) \nHealth expectancies at birth &amp; at age 65 in the United Kingdom\n The Kings Fund (2012) \nLong-term conditions and mental health: The cost of co-morbidities\n